Program: Outlook
Title: Nobel Winner: Saving India's children
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p02hrf50
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 4 Feb 2015
Kailash Satyarthi: the Nobel prize winner risking his life to save children from slavery. The Brazilian rap star Criolo. Anita Weinstein, a survivor of the attack on the Jewish Centre in Buenos Aires. The British extreme swimmer Lewis Pugh whose latest challenge is said to be one of the most dangerous swims ever undertaken by a human: swimming the Ross Sea in Antarctica. Show less